"#multipleLinearRegression"
""
"1.MLR talks about the relationship between two or more independent variables and one dependent variable say for example salary of a person in a company can be modeled as MLR because it depends on so many factors such as past experience, technical background, age, etc."
""
"2.The mathematics involved behind it assumes that each independent variables can be modeled as independent linear regression as y1 = m1x1+c1,"
"y2 = m2x2+c2,y3=m3x3+c3,... so on summing which yields result y=m1x1+m2x2+m3x3c where c = c1+c2+c3...and x1,x2,x3 are independent variables which are considered while predicting y values."
""
"3.The model is implemented by importing linear regression from the sci-kit learn library and accordingly predicting values on test data."
""
"4.Advantages & disadvantages involving MLR
